# ThreadSanitizer suppression file for nim-debra DWCAS contention tests.
#
# Policy (design §7.3): max 5 pre-existing-race entries.
#
# Branch B tripwire: if reaching a green TSAN run requires MORE than 5
# suppressions, the implementation phase STOPS and surfaces to the
# operator via AskUserQuestion. The threshold is deliberately tight —
# exceeding it means TSAN attachment surfaced a structural problem
# with Nim's runtime under DWCAS workloads, which is out of scope for
# v0.10.0.
#
# Branch C (operator-approved fallback): ship v0.10.0 without TSAN
# coverage, documenting the gap in CHANGELOG ## Known Gaps and filing
# a tracking issue for v0.10.1.
#
# Each entry MUST be annotated with:
#   - The exact stack frame (`fun:<symbol>` or `race:<file>:<line>`)
#   - A one-line justification
#   - A category tag: pre-existing-nim-runtime, pre-existing-test-harness, or false-positive
#
# DWCAS-attributed race policy: any race whose stack contains a frame
# from src/debra/atomics.nim DWCAS code paths is a RELEASE BLOCKER
# regardless of the suppression budget. The success metric is "zero
# unsuppressed races on DWCAS-attributed call frames over ≥ 10,000
# iterations" (design §7.3).
#
# Suppressions below this line:
